author: @tuedoongjjang7289
text:
People are not used to this kind of concept and genre, Alcohol-Free is not your typical K-pop summer song, and if i'm not mistaken TWICE is the first one to pull out this kind of genre in k-pop for a title track, that's probably the reason why some people think it sounds bad. You know these kind of people when they always hear the same typical sounds, the fresh sounds won't be in their preferences. After all it's a c'hill lounge music' so why would they look for an impactful or energetic chorus. And why chill music cannot be a title track.

In this k-pop world that is full of EDM, Synth-Pop or Bubblegum pop, we have TWICE here pulling out something new Alcohol-free is an oasis in k-pop.

author: @yangpunyaakunasli1908
text: Anyone who said this is a bad song and missing something is either antis, haters or theres something with their ears. This is honestly one of the best title track Twice ever had. JYP pd-nim gave everything in this title track ; fair line distribution, great composing, great choreography, great theme and overall perfect summer song. If you listen carefully, you can really hear how great pd-nim on composing this song. Its a whole different song than DTNA and i fully love it! If DTNA is the song to dance to when you’re outside playing on the beach, Alcohol-Free is the song that you play in your car on your way to the beach or in midnight bar dancing with your friends. I’ll give this song : 9/10
